.TH CCS 1 "March 2026" "ccs 2.2.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
ccs \- Claude Code Session manager
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ccs
.RI [ command ]
.RI [ \-\- ]
.RI [ args... ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ccs
manages Claude Code sessions inside dedicated tmux sessions with
descriptions, fuzzy-match attach, and scheduled cron jobs.
.PP
Sessions run on a dedicated tmux socket
.RB ( ccs ),
isolated from regular tmux usage. Mouse scrolling, truecolor, and
50k-line scrollback are configured automatically.
.PP
ANSI colors are disabled when stdout is not a terminal or when the
.B NO_COLOR
environment variable is set.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.BR new " [" name "] [" description ]
Start a new Claude Code session. Name defaults to the current
directory basename. Names must start with a letter or digit,
followed by letters, digits, hyphens, or underscores.
.TP
.B ls
List all active sessions grouped by working directory.
Automatically cleans up orphaned metadata entries.
.TP
.BR a ", " attach " [" name ]
Attach to a session. Supports partial, case\-insensitive matching.
If only one session exists, attaches directly.
.TP
.BR kill " " name
Kill a session (with confirmation).
.TP
.B gc
Clean up orphaned session metadata (entries for sessions
that no longer exist in tmux).
.TP
.B schedule add
Interactive wizard to create a scheduled cron job.
.TP
.B schedule ls
List all scheduled jobs with status.
.TP
.BR "schedule rm" " " name
Remove a scheduled job. Fails if the named schedule does not exist.
.TP
.B log
Show cron execution history (last 40 entries).
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version
Print version.
.PP
All commands that take positional arguments accept
.B \-\-
to separate options from arguments.
.SH SMART DISPATCH
Running
.B ccs
with no arguments behaves contextually:
no sessions shows help, one session attaches directly,
multiple sessions lists them.
.SH EXIT CODES
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
General error (session not found, file missing, etc.).
.TP
.B 2
Usage error (invalid arguments, bad session name).
.SH TAB COMPLETION
Bash and zsh completions are installed automatically with the
deb package. They provide completion for commands, session names,
and schedule names.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/ccs/sessions.meta
Session metadata (name, description, directory).
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/ccs/schedules.meta
Scheduled job definitions.
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/ccs/cron.log
Cron execution log (auto\-rotated at 1000 lines).
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B CCS_DATA_DIR
Override the data directory (default: $XDG_DATA_HOME/ccs).
.TP
.B CCS_SOCKET
Override the tmux socket name (default: ccs).
.TP
.B XDG_DATA_HOME
Base directory for application data (default: ~/.local/share).
.TP
.B NO_COLOR
If set (to any value), disables colored output.
See https://no\-color.org.
.SH DEPENDENCIES
.BR tmux (1),
.BR bash (1),
.BR cron (8)
.SH AUTHOR
Robin <robin@nurrobin.de>
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR tmux (1),
.BR crontab (5)
